If a dog has a medically diagnosed grain allergy or intolerance (confirmed by a vet), grain-free can help reduce itching, GI upset, or skin issues.

Some individual dogs don‚Äôt tolerate certain grains well ‚Äî not because grains are inherently bad, but because that dog reacts poorly.

‚úî Third: Consult your vet if considering grain-free ‚Äî especially if switching from a grain-inclusive diet

üìå Bottom Line: Is Grain-Free Good?

Not inherently.
